modules.description: Provides file system operations such as reading, writing, and deleting files, along with directory traversal and file metadata retrieval. Works with file paths, file handles, and binary or text data streams. Used to manage app-specific storage, cache files, and access device file systems in mobile applications.

Returns absolute paths to various device-specific directories used for storing app data, caches, and files. Operates on string-based file system paths relevant to mobile application development. Used to organize file storage, manage temporary files, and access shared or synchronized data locations.
